---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const startDate = new Date('2014-04-01');
const today = new Date();
const yearsExp = Math.floor((today.getTime() - startDate.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365.25));
const expLabel = `${yearsExp}+ years`;
---
<Layout
  title="Microsoft 365 Services · AroraMSP"
  description={`M365 migrations, tenant setup, security hardening, and license optimization. Fixed-fee consulting from a senior Microsoft engineer with ${expLabel} of hands-on experience.`}
  page="services"
  canonical="https://aroramsp.com/services"
  ogTitle="Microsoft 365 Services - AroraMSP"
  ogDescription={`M365 migrations, tenant setup, security hardening, and license optimization. Fixed-fee consulting from a senior Microsoft engineer with ${expLabel} of hands-on experience.`}
>
  <section class="page wrap">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="sec-label">// services</div>
      <h2>Microsoft 365 expertise, without the overhead of a large firm.</h2>
      <p>Four focused services covering every stage of your M365 environment. Fixed fees, no reselling, and direct access to a senior Microsoft engineer with {expLabel} of hands-on experience supporting enterprise tenants globally.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="services">
      <div class="service reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="n"><span>01</span><span class="tag">migration</span></div>
        <h3>Migrate to Microsoft 365</h3>
        <p>Move from Google Workspace, on-premises Exchange, or another Microsoft tenant with no downtime and no data loss. Your users stay productive throughout the cutover.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cutover, staged, and hybrid migration paths</li>
          <li>Mailbox, OneDrive, SharePoint, and Teams data</li>
          <li>Entra ID and identity migration</li>
          <li>Cross-tenant and domain consolidation</li>
          <li>DNS cutover and mail flow verification</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="service reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="n"><span>02</span><span class="tag">setup</span></div>
        <h3>Tenant Setup and Configuration</h3>
        <p>A correctly built Microsoft 365 tenant from day one. Identity, email, collaboration, and security configured to Microsoft best practice, not factory defaults that leave gaps your team will spend months closing.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Entra ID with Conditional Access and MFA</li>
          <li>Exchange Online with SPF, DKIM, DMARC, MTA-STS</li>
          <li>Teams and SharePoint governance baseline</li>
          <li>Intune device management policies</li>
          <li>Admin role separation and break-glass accounts</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="service reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <div class="n"><span>03</span><span class="tag">security</span></div>
        <h3>Security Hardening</h3>
        <p>Close the security gaps that accumulate when Microsoft 365 is deployed quickly or managed reactively. Defender, Purview, and Intune configured to protect your users and your data against real threats, not checkbox compliance.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>MFA and passwordless authentication rollout</li>
          <li>Conditional Access policy design and enforcement</li>
          <li>Microsoft Defender for Business configuration</li>
          <li>Data Loss Prevention and sensitivity labels</li>
          <li>Endpoint compliance policies with Intune</li>
          <li>Privileged Identity Management</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="service reveal reveal-delay-4">
        <div class="n"><span>04</span><span class="tag">optimize</span></div>
        <h3>License Optimization</h3>
        <p>Most SMBs overpay between 20% and 40% on Microsoft 365 licensing. A line-by-line audit identifies unused licenses, wrong tiers, and redundant add-ons, then produces a concrete savings plan you can act on immediately.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full license inventory across all SKUs</li>
          <li>User-by-user utilization mapping</li>
          <li>Right-sizing between E3, E5, and Business tiers</li>
          <li>Add-on and third-party overlap analysis</li>
          <li>Renewal and co-term timing strategy</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
